					<p>
						Writing an essay (preferred):<br />
						I would like to invite you to participate with an essay reflecting on
						your practice and your thoughts and views on AI. The following questions
						may serve as a guide or inspiration for your writing:
					</p>

					<ul>
						<li>
							Why is AI interesting for your artistic practice/work? What did
							you hope to achieve when you decided to work with AI?
						</li>
						<li>
							How do you work with AI algorithms? What are the roles of you and
							AI in your collaboration?
						</li>
						<li>
							What workflow/methodology/tools do you use to create this
							collaboration? Where do these methods appear in your work?
						</li>
						<li>
							What do you think your (artistic) practice reveals about the
							"creativity" embedded in the algorithms used in AI?
						</li>
						<li>How does AI fit into the broader context of (art) history?</li>
						<li>
							How does your work reflect (critically) on the current state of
							AI?
						</li>
					</ul>

					<p>
						I would like to point out that these questions should serve as
						helpful inspiration, but it is not necessary to answer them. In the
						end, you are free to write what you think is best for the
						publication. In addition, I would encourage you to use images in
						your essays to help present your ideas better. Especially,
						references to your previous (artistic) work are always welcome.
					</p>

