					<h2 class="mobile-indent">About the publication</h2>
				</div>
				<div class="content__section-text">
					<p>
						The publication will exist in a hybrid form. This means that it will
						exist as a website and as a printed book. Using web-to-print
						technology, the printed version will be generated based on the web
						version. Because web technology was not designed to create print
						layouts and documents, this creates friction and perhaps even
						errors. The friction created by the digital and physical existence
						of the publication metaphorically represents the friction and
						differences between human creativity and artificial creativity,
						between human intelligence and artificial intelligence.
					</p>

					<p>
						In addition, AI will also play a critical role in the editorial
						decisions that are made in the publication. Commenting on the
						current overuse of chat interfaces as the main way to interact with
						generative AI, the publication will also exist as a chat interface.
						This allows the model to curate the content of the publication based
						on search queries provided by the reader. Using a technology called
						<a
							href="https://proceedings.neurips.cc/paper/2020/file/6b493230205f780e1bc26945df7481e5-Paper.pdf"
							>Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)</a
						>, the model can index and understand the publication and navigate
						the reader to articles that are relevant to their query.
					</p>

					<p>
						Because you, the participant, form the knowledge base that the AI
						models refer to, you control the behaviour and responses of the
						model. Keep this in mind as you write, and feel free to think of
						your writing as an experimental approach to creating moments of
						surprise for both the AI model and the readers. ðŸ˜‰
